  "texts": [
    "Sub-words are called Pieces of Arabic Word (PAW).",
    "A PAW could consist of a single character or a set of linked characters.",
    "Another distinctive feature of the Arabic script is the presence of diacritical marks, which can be points or signs.",
    "Diacritical points are crucial in determining the identity of characters, serving to provide additional information or modify the pronunciation of the character.",
    "Out of the 28 characters, 16 of them contain diacritical points positioned above or below the main body of the character."
  ],
